The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Friday, March 05, 2004  Nation at a Glance				 																10 undertrials escape in GujaratAhmedabad: Ten petty criminals lodged in Borsad sub-jail in Anand district escaped on Wednesday night after tricking guards into opening their cell and severely injuring two of them, reports our correspondent.				 																Court clears film on riots				 																																																	Mumbai (PTI): Bombay High Court has directed Doordarshan to telecast national award winning documentary Father, Son and Holy War within 12 weeks and asked the Central Board of Film Certification to grant licence to Akrosh, a film based on the Gujarat riots.				 																																																										The board had refused to grant licence to Akrosh on the ground that it was biased and projected a particular community. However, director Ramesh Pimple argued that during the riots only a particular community was targeted and the film had focussed on this aspect.				 																Gangsters arrested				 																																																	Mumbai (PTI): Mumbai polices crime branch has arrested three members of the Chhota Rajan gang when they were allegedly attempting to kill a member of a rival gang at Goregaon on Wednesday evening, police said.				 																Fire kills 1Sonepat (PTI): One person was killed and goods worth Rs 50,000 destroyed in a fire that broke out in a house in Tharu village following a short circuit. The victim, Jagdish, was fast asleep when the fire broke out on Wednesday night.				 																Ship trip put off				 																																																	Kochi (PTI): Nearly 150 passengers of MV Bharat Seema plying between Kochi and the Lakshadweep Islands were stranded when the ships trip was cancelled on Thursday morning. The cancellation followed an indefinite fast by the vessels crew to protest the transfer of its management.				 																Father, child drownMachilipatnam (PTI): A man and his four-year-old son drowned, while his wife and another person were able to swim ashore when a boat capsized in a fish tank near Nadigoanlanka in Krishna district.				 																Communal clashVadodara (PTI): Violence erupted afresh on Thursday when one person was stabbed in the Yakoutpura area of the city. Police lobbed teargas shells to disperse members of two communities, who indulged in stone-throwing. One autorickshaw was torched by the mob.																		Over 4.62 lakh pilgrims from various parts of the country have visited the Vaishnodevi shrine since January. This is an increase of over 1.10 lakh pilgrims compared to the corresponding period last year.
